1. By the peoples antient Right in Edward the Confeſſors time, or before, in their Folkmote to chuſe an Heretoke (a Baron or perſon of Quality) in every County, in nature of a Captain, who had the power of the County and Militia in every Shire, ficut et Vicecomites Provinciarum et Comitatuum eligi debent per ſingulos Comitatus in pleno Folkmoto: as Sheriffs of Provinces and Counties ought to be choſen in every County;
                as you may read at large in Mr. Lambards Archaion, f. 135. de Hetetochiis; in Sir Henry Spelmans Gloſſarium, Dux & Heretochius, p. 232, 348, 349.

My Soveraign Power of Parliaments, part 2. p. 24, 25. Cooks 2 Inſtitutes, p. 174, 175.
